#: ../../source/methods/external_parameter_orthogonalization.rst:2
msgid "ExternalParameterOrthogonalization"
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:1
#: of
msgid ""
"Bases: :py:class:`~sklearn.base.TransformerMixin`, "
":py:class:`~sklearn.base.BaseEstimator`"
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:1
#: of
msgid ""
"Remove variation linked to known external nuisance parameters using "
"External Parameter Orthogonalization (EPO) [1]_."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:4
#: of
msgid ""
"EPO is designed for situations where spectral measurements are affected "
"by controlled external factors (e.g., temperature, humidity, instrument "
"differences) that are not related to the target property. The method "
"estimates a nuisance subspace from an auxiliary dataset or from "
"structured replicates in which the external parameter varies while the "
"underlying sample composition is held constant."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:11
#: of
msgid ""
"A matrix capturing this external variation is constructed (e.g., from "
"differences or deviations within replicate groups), and its dominant "
"components are obtained via SVD/PCA. These components define a subspace "
"associated with the external parameter. A projection operator is then "
"applied to X to remove variation in this subspace."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:17
#: of
msgid ""
"When ``sample_ids`` are provided, the external-effect matrix is formed "
"from within-sample deviations (i.e., each spectrum minus its sample "
"mean), isolating variation due to the external parameter from chemical "
"variation."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:21
#: of
msgid ""
"The transformer preserves the original number of features and is intended"
" as a signal correction step rather than dimensionality reduction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/methods/external_parameter_orthogonalization.rst
#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.fit
#: of
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:24
#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:98
#: of
msgid "Number of orthogonal components to remove. Must be a positive integer."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:26
#: of
msgid ""
"Placeholder argument kept for API compatibility with scikit-learn style "
"estimators. Input validation currently relies on the default behavior of "
"the underlying validation utilities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/methods/external_parameter_orthogonalization.rst
msgid "Variables"
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:31
#: of
msgid "Mean spectrum computed from the calibration data passed to `fit()`."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:34
#: of
msgid ""
"Orthogonal projection matrix used to suppress nuisance variation. "
"Applying `X_centered @ P_epo_` removes the subspace spanned by the first "
"`n_components` singular vectors of the external variation matrix."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:39
#: of
msgid "Number of features seen during `fit()`."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:43
#: of
msgid "References"
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:44
#: of
msgid ""
"Jean-Michel Roger, Fabien Chauchard, Veronique Bellon-Maurel (2003), "
"EPO–PLS external parameter orthogonalisation of PLS application to "
"temperature-independent measurement of sugar content of intact fruits, "
"Chemometrics and Intelligent Laboratory Systems, Volume 66, Issue 2, "
"Pages 191-204, https://doi.org/10.1016/S0169-7439(03)00051-0"
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:52
#: of
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:65
#: of
msgid ""
"Repeated measurements of the same physical sample can be grouped through "
"`sample_ids` so that the nuisance subspace is estimated from within-"
"sample differences only."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:75
#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.fit:22
#: of
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:76
#: of
msgid ""
"EPO is commonly used when spectral measurements are affected by known "
"nuisance sources such as temperature, instrument transfer, humidity, or "
"acquisition conditions. The nuisance structure is estimated from "
"`X_external`, then projected out from `X`."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:81
#: of
msgid ""
"If `sample_ids` are provided, the difference matrix is built from "
"deviations around the mean spectrum of each repeated sample. This "
"isolates variation due to the external condition while suppressing the "
"underlying chemical signal."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:85
#: of
msgid ""
"The transformer preserves the original number of features. It performs "
"signal correction, not dimensionality reduction."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:90
#: of
msgid ":py:obj:`chemotools.projection.OrthogonalSignalCorrection`"
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:91
#: of
msgid "Remove variation orthogonal to a supervised target."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:93
#: of
msgid ":py:obj:`sklearn.pipeline.make_pipeline`"
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:94
#: of
msgid "Compose EPO with downstream estimators."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:96
#: of
msgid "Initialize the External Parameter Orthogonalization (EPO) transformer."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization:100
#: of
msgid "Whether to copy X and Y in fit before applying centering."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.fit:1
#: of
msgid "Fit the EPO projection from calibration and nuisance spectra."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.fit:3
#: of
msgid ""
"Calibration spectra that will later be corrected by the learned EPO "
"projection."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.fit:6
#: of
msgid "Ignored. Present for scikit-learn API compatibility."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.fit:8
#: of
msgid ""
"Spectra describing the nuisance variation to remove. These may be the "
"same samples measured under perturbed external conditions, transfer "
"standards, or any dataset representative of the unwanted subspace."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.fit:12
#: of
msgid ""
"Optional identifiers linking repeated measurements of the same sample. "
"When provided, the nuisance difference matrix is computed within each "
"sample group, which helps isolate external variation from chemical "
"differences between samples."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/methods/external_parameter_orthogonalization.rst
#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.fit
#: of
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.fit:18
#: of
msgid "**self** -- Fitted estimator storing the projection matrix in `P_epo_`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/methods/external_parameter_orthogonalization.rst
#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.fit
#: of
msgid "Return type"
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.fit:23
#: of
msgid ""
"The nuisance variation matrix $D$ is constructed as either centered "
"`X_external` or within-group deviations when `sample_ids` are available. "
"A singular value decomposition of $D$ yields the dominant nuisance "
"directions, and the projection matrix is then defined as $P = I - VV^T$."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.transform:1
#: of
msgid "Project spectra onto the subspace orthogonal to nuisance variation."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.transform:3
#: of
msgid "Spectra to correct."
msgstr ""

#: chemotools.projection._external_parameter_orthogonalization.ExternalParameterOrthogonalization.transform:6
#: of
msgid ""
"Corrected spectra after centering with `mean_X_` and projection with "
"`P_epo_`."
msgstr ""

